(power_switching, time).explanation: Switching power and execution time are independent metrics where switching power represents dynamic energy consumption while execution time measures performance, with no direct causal relationship between them;

(power_switching, power_clock).explanation: Switching power and clock power are separate components of total power consumption in digital circuits, representing different power dissipation mechanisms without direct causal influence;

(power_switching, area_net_area).explanation: Larger interconnect area increases wire capacitance which directly increases the switching power required to charge and discharge these capacitive loads during signal transitions;
